│ instruction. The `OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs` logic iterates through the resolver's basic    │
│ blocks, looking for `return` instructions to identify the set of possible functions        │
│ (versions) that the `ifunc` can resolve to. When it encounters a resolver like `@f1` with  │
│ no `return` instructions, it fails to collect any versions. This leads to an empty         │
│ `Callees` vector, which subsequently triggers an assertion `!Callees.empty()`, causing the │
